- Deliveroo search page listing is not supported yet.

issue.title: feat(HungryHouse): Display ratings for search list
issue.body:
- Able to display ratings for Hungryhouse search lists. Hungry House
  does not contain the postcode in the search list page. To solve this,
  get the URL for the individual takeaway from the search page. Load the
  HTML DOM of the individual takeaway and search the DOM for the
  postcode. Use the name from the search page and the postcode to get
  the FSA rating for the takeaway.

- Postcode validation for the HH Search page.

(fix): FSA Rating fetch

- When an array (more than 1 result) was returned for takeaways matching
  the name and the postcode by the FSA Json API, an error caused the
  rating to be undefined. Fix this problem by checking if the result
  returned is an array or a take away. If its an array, get the rating
  from the first element in the array.

- Remove a lot of console.log statements that were used for debugging

[Version: 1.2.0.1]

[QA]
Has tests: No
Reviewed by: Nil

issue.title: feat(just-eat): Add rating for individual TA view
issue.body:
- Previously for Just-Eat only the search listings had ratings next to
  them. This update is able to display the rating for an individual
  takeaway when it's menu is being viewed.

- Remove some comments

- Add a much neater interface for handling the message passing with the
  background script for getting takeaway JSON rating. Will add a
  parameter for passing in a callback function instead of hardcoding a
  callback

- Added several constants for hardcoded classnames

- Improve the README by adding images

[QA]
Has tests: No
Reviewed by: Nil
